The paper deals with Slepian-Wolf coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves channel coding and decoding (cs.CC), as well as side information (cs.SI). The paper proposes a universal decoder that does not depend on the statistics of the sources or the channel, which could be seen as a machine learning or data science approach (cs.DS). Finally, the paper considers a full Slepian-Wolf coding scenario, which involves joint decoding of two source streams, which could be seen as a problem in machine learning or statistical inference (cs.LG).
